00:50:12,982 --> 00:50:13,982
How should I put it?

778
00:50:16,052 --> 00:50:17,052
Not even for a single moment...

779
00:50:17,822 --> 00:50:19,562
was she ever a real mother to me.

780
00:50:23,992 --> 00:50:25,262
How could she be like that?

781
00:50:26,132 --> 00:50:28,172
She's raised you since you were five.

782
00:50:29,732 --> 00:50:30,842
Some people are just like that.

783
00:50:32,172 --> 00:50:34,142
That's why I'm so fond of your parents.

784
00:50:35,442 --> 00:50:36,442
I bet...

785
00:50:36,812 --> 00:50:39,682
I got more love from your mother than I ever did from mine.

786
00:50:43,482 --> 00:50:47,052
So, were you mistreated growing up?

787
00:50:49,252 --> 00:50:50,822
If she had at least mistreated me,

788
00:50:51,992 --> 00:50:53,592
my father would have noticed.

789
00:50:57,392 --> 00:50:58,402
She would smile,

790
00:50:59,432 --> 00:51:01,172
but she was like thin ice.

791
00:51:03,332 --> 00:51:05,872
Someone can smile and be like thin ice?

792
00:51:07,872 --> 00:51:08,872
Let go of me!

793
00:51:09,612 --> 00:51:12,712
My mom, my dad, my brothers,

794
00:51:14,312 --> 00:51:15,312
and my grandmother...

795
00:51:16,282 --> 00:51:17,622
all love me dearly. I'm precious to them,

796
00:51:18,822 --> 00:51:20,152
so don't you dare treat me like this again.

797
00:51:25,162 --> 00:51:28,632
I raised him since he was five. So I'm not his real mother?

798
00:51:29,762 --> 00:51:31,102
I am Seong Jae's mother.

799
00:51:31,532 --> 00:51:35,102
